Albena Denkova.label: Albena Denkova
Albena Denkova.description: Albena Denkova is a Bulgarian ice dancer. With partner and fiance Maxim Staviski, she is a two-time World champion, a two-time European silver medalist, and the 2006 Grand Prix Final champion. Wikipedia

Alexei Tikhonov.label: Alexei Tikhonov
Alexei Tikhonov.description: Alexei Vladimirovich Tikhonov is a Russian pair skater. With partner Maria Petrova, he is the 2000 World champion and a two-time European champion. Wikipedia

Annette Dytrt.label: Annette Dytrt
Annette Dytrt.description: Annette Dytrt is a German figure skater who has also competed internationally for the Czech Republic. She won the 1999 Czech Figure Skating Championships and is the 2003–2006 German national champion. Wikipedia

Anett Pötzsch.label: Anett Pötzsch
Anett Pötzsch.description:
Anett Pötzsch is a retired German figure skater. She is the 1980 Olympic champion, two-time World champion, four-time European champion, and five-time East German champion.
Her first name is sometimes incorrectly spelled "Annett." Wikipedia

Artur Dmitriev.label: Artur Dmitriev
Artur Dmitriev.description: Artur Valeryevich Dmitriev is a Russian pair skater who competed internationally for the Soviet Union, the Unified Team, and Russia. Wikipedia

Brian Joubert.label: Brian Joubert
Brian Joubert.description: Brian Joubert is a French figure skater. He is the 2007 World Champion, a three-time European champion, an eight-time French National champion, and the 2006-7 Grand Prix Final champion. Wikipedia

Carlo Fassi.label: Carlo Fassi
Carlo Fassi.description: Carlo Fassi was a well-known Italian figure skater and international coach whose students included several World and Olympic champions. Wikipedia

Carolina Kostner.label: Carolina Kostner
Carolina Kostner.description: Carolina Kostner is an Italian figure skater. She is the 2014 Olympic bronze medalist, the 2012 World champion, a five-time European champion, and the 2011 Grand Prix Final champion. Wikipedia

Claudia Leistner.label: Claudia Leistner
Claudia Leistner.description: Claudia Leistner, married name Pfrengle, is a German figure skater. She is a two-time World silver medalist and the 1989 European champion. Wikipedia

Dorothy Hamill.label: Dorothy Hamill
Dorothy Hamill.description: Dorothy Stuart Hamill is an American figure skater. She is the 1976 Olympic champion in ladies' singles and the 1976 World champion. Wikipedia

Elsa Rendschmidt.label: Elsa Rendschmidt
Elsa Rendschmidt.description:
Elsa Rendschmidt was a German figure skater and the first German woman to win a medal at the Olympic Games.
Rendschmidt won the silver medal at the 1908 Summer Olympics, the first Olympics to include a ladies' figure skating event. Wikipedia

Erich Buck.label: Erich Buck
Erich Buck.description: Erich Buck is a German former ice dancer who competed for West Germany. With his sister Angelika Buck, he is the 1972 European champion, a four-time World medalist, and a six-time West German national champion. Wikipedia

Eva Pawlik.label: Eva Pawlik
Eva Pawlik.description: Eva Pawlik was an Austrian figure skater, a show star, an actress and the first European figure skater to be a TV figure skating commentator. Wikipedia

Eva Romanová.label: Eva Romanová
Eva Romanová.description: Eva Romanová is a former Czech figure skater. Together with her brother Pavel Roman, she won four World Figure Skating Championships titles in ice dancing. Wikipedia

Evgeni Plushenko.label: Evgeni Plushenko
Evgeni Plushenko.description: Evgeni Viktorovich Plushenko is a retired Russian figure skater. He is the 2006 Olympic gold medalist, 2014 Olympic team gold medalist, 2002 Olympic silver medalist, and 2010 Olympic silver medalist, ... Wikipedia

Gabriele Seyfert.label: Gabriele Seyfert
Gabriele Seyfert.description: Gabriele Seyfert is a retired German figure skater. She is a two-time World champion, and the 1968 Olympic silver medalist. Wikipedia

Gundi Busch.label: Gundi Busch
Gundi Busch.description: Gundula "Gundi" Busch was a German figure skater and coach. She was the first World champion ladies' singles champion representing Germany. She took part in the 1952 Winter Olympics in Oslo and finished 8th in the Ladies Singles. Wikipedia

Gwendal Peizerat.label: Gwendal Peizerat
Gwendal Peizerat.description: Gwendal Peizerat is a French ice dancer. With Marina Anissina, he is the 2002 Olympic champion, the 1998 Olympic bronze medalist, the 2000 World Champion, and a six-time French National Champion. Wikipedia

Hana Mašková.label: Hana Mašková
Hana Mašková.description: Hana Mašková was a Czech figure skater who competed for Czechoslovakia. She was the 1968 Olympic bronze medalist, a two-time World bronze medalist, and the 1968 European champion. Wikipedia

Hendryk Schamberger.label: Hendryk Schamberger
Hendryk Schamberger.description: Hendryk Schamberger is a German former competitive ice dancer. With Jennifer Goolsbee, he is a four-time German national champion and placed ninth at the 1994 Winter Olympics. Wikipedia

Ilia Kulik.label: Ilia Kulik
Ilia Kulik.description: Ilia Alexandrovich Kulik is a Russian figure skater. He is the 1998 Olympic Champion, the 1995 European Champion, the 1997–1998 Grand Prix Final champion, and the 1995 World Junior champion. Wikipedia

Irina Slutskaya.label: Irina Slutskaya
Irina Slutskaya.description: Irina Eduardovna Slutskaya is a Russian figure skater. She is a two-time World champion, two-time Olympic medalist, seven-time European Champion, a four-time Grand Prix Final Champion and a four-time Russian National Champion. Wikipedia

Júlia Sebestyén.label: Júlia Sebestyén
Júlia Sebestyén.description: Júlia Sebestyén is a Hungarian figure skater. She is the 2004 European Champion and 2002–2010 Hungarian national champion. At the 2004 European Figure Skating Championships, she became the first Hungarian woman to win the European title. Wikipedia

John Curry.label: John Curry
John Curry.description: John Anthony Curry, OBE was a British figure skater. He was the 1976 Olympic and World Champion. He was famous for combining ballet and modern dance influences into his skating. Wikipedia
Awards: BBC Sports Personality of the Year Award

Julia Pfrengle.label: Julia Pfrengle
Julia Pfrengle.description: Julia Pfrengle is a German figure skater. She is the 2010 German bronze medalist and 2009 junior national champion. Her win in 2009 was her third consecutive national title, and her first at the junior level. Wikipedia

Kiira Korpi.label: Kiira Korpi
Kiira Korpi.description: Kiira Linda Katriina Korpi is a Finnish figure skater. She is a three-time European medalist, the 2010 Trophée Eric Bompard champion, the 2012 Rostelecom Cup champion, a two-time Cup of China medalist, and a four-time Finnish national champion. Wikipedia

Kim Yu-Na.label: Kim Yuna
Kim Yu-Na.description: Kim Yuna is a retired South Korean figure skater. She is the 2010 Olympic champion and 2014 silver medalist in ladies' singles; the 2009, 2013 World champion; the 2009 Four Continents champion; a ... Wikipedia

Kimmie Meissner.label: Kimmie Meissner
Kimmie Meissner.description: Kimberly Claire "Kimmie" Meissner is an American figure skater. She is the 2006 World champion, the 2007 U.S. national champion, and the 2007 Four Continents champion. Wikipedia
Kimmie Meissner.Born: October 4, 1989 (age 24), Towson, Baltimore, Maryland, United States

Kristi Yamaguchi.label: Kristi Yamaguchi
Kristi Yamaguchi.description: Kristine Tsuya "Kristi" Yamaguchi is an American figure skater. She is the 1992 Olympic Champion in ladies' singles. Yamaguchi also won two World Figure Skating Championships in 1991 and 1992 and a U.S. Figure Skating Championships in 1992. Wikipedia

Ludowika Jakobsson.label: Ludowika Jakobsson
Ludowika Jakobsson.description: Ludowika Jakobsson was a German-Finnish figure skater. Competing in pair skating with skating partner and husband Walter Jakobsson, she became Olympic Champion in 1920 and three-time World champion. Wikipedia

Mao Asada.label: Mao Asada
Mao Asada.description: Mao Asada is a Japanese competitive figure skater and an Olympic silver medalist noted for her smooth skating skills and triple axel jumps. Wikipedia

Marina Anissina.label: Marina Anisina
Marina Anissina.description: Marina Vyacheslavovna Anissina is a French-Russian ice dancer. With partner Gwendal Peizerat, she is the 2002 Olympic champion. Wikipedia

Marina Kielmann.label: Marina Kielmann
Marina Kielmann.description: Marina Kielmann is a former figure skater from Germany. She won the gold medal in ladies singles at the German Figure Skating Championships three times, from 1991 to 1993 and competed in the Winter Olympics in 1988 and 1992. Wikipedia

Martin Liebers.label: Martin Liebers
Martin Liebers.description:
Martin Liebers is a German figure skater. He is a four-time German national bronze medalist, was the Junior National Champion in 2000 and the Novice National Champion in 1997.
In 2009 he started training pairs. Wikipedia

Maya Usova.label: Maya Usova
Maya Usova.description: Maya Valentinovna Usova is a Russian former ice dancer. With Alexander Zhulin, she is a two-time Olympic medalist, the 1993 World champion, and the 1993 European champion. Wikipedia

Michael Huth.label: Michael Huth
Michael Huth.description: Michael Huth is a German figure skating and former competitor for East Germany. Wikipedia

Michelle Kwan.label: Michelle Kwan
Michelle Kwan.description: Michelle Wingshan Kwan is a retired American figure skater. She is a two-time Olympic medalist, a five-time World champion and a nine-time U.S. champion. Wikipedia
Education: The Fletcher School of Law and Diplomacy (2009–2011)
Josef Korbel School of International Studies (2006–2009)
Rim of the World High School (1998)

Norman Jeschke.label: Norman Jeschke
Norman Jeschke.description: Norman Jeschke is a German pair skater. Wikipedia

Ondrej Nepela.label: Ondrej Nepela
Ondrej Nepela.description: Ondrej Nepela was a Slovak figure skater who represented Czechoslovakia. He was the 1972 Olympic champion, a three-time World champion, and a five-time European champion. Later in his career, he performed professionally and became a coach. Wikipedia

Oksana Baiul.label: Oksana Baiul
Oksana Baiul.description: Oksana Baiul is a retired Ukrainian figure skater. She is the 1993 World champion and the 1994 Olympic champion in ladies' singles. Baiul is the first and so far the only skater to win gold at the Winter Olympics representing Ukraine. Wikipedia
Movies and TV shows: The Cutting Edge Going for the Gold
Olympic Figure Skating Greatest Performances in History Vol. 1More

Patrick Meier.label: Patrick Meier
Patrick Meier.description:
Patrick Meier is a Swiss figure skater. He is a multiple Swiss national champion.
Meier began skating at the age of six. Wikipedia

Paul Boll.label: Paul Boll
Paul Boll.description: Paul Boll is a German ice dancer. With former partner Tanja Kolbe, he is the 2006 German junior national champion and placed 16th at the 2006 World Junior Championships. Wikipedia

Peter Liebers.label: Peter Liebers
Peter Liebers.description: Peter Liebers is a German figure skater. He is the 2010 Nebelhorn Trophy bronze medalist, the 2012 Ice Challenge champion, and a five-time German national champion. Wikipedia

Ria Baran.label: Ria Baran
Ria Baran.description:
Ria Baran was a German pair skater. She skated together with Paul Falk and became twice World champion and in 1952 Olympic champion.
Ria Baran married Paul Falk during her active international figure skating. Wikipedia

Robin Szolkowy.label: Robin Szolkowy
Robin Szolkowy.description: Robin Szolkowy is a German pair skater. With partner Aliona Savchenko, he is the 2010 and 2014 Olympic bronze medalist, a four-time World Champion, a four-time European Champion, a three-time Grand Prix ... Wikipedia

Rosalynn Sumners.label: Rosalynn Sumners
Rosalynn Sumners.description: Rosalynn Diane Sumners is an American ladies' singles figure skater. She was the World Junior champion in 1980, the U.S. National champion in 1982, 1983 and 1984, World champion in 1983, and won a silver medal at the 1984 Winter Olympics. Wikipedia
Rosalynn Sumners.Born: April 20, 1964 (age 49), Palo Alto, California, United States

Rudi Cerne.label: Rudi Cerne
Rudi Cerne.description:
Rudolf "Rudi" Cerne was a German figure skater and now works as a TV presenter.
His father, a figure skater himself, brought him onto the ice when he was six years old. He skated for the club Herner EV and represented West Germany. Wikipedia

Sabine Baeß.label: Sabine Baeß
Sabine Baeß.description: Sabine Baeß, married Marbach, is a German pair skater. With partner Tassilo Thierbach, she is the 1982 World Champion, and two-time European Champion. Wikipedia

Sasha Cohen.label: Sasha Cohen
Sasha Cohen.description: Alexandra Pauline "Sasha" Cohen is a U.S. figure skater. She is the 2006 Olympic silver medalist, a three-time World Championship medalist, the 2003 Grand Prix Final Champion, and the 2006 U.S. Champion. Wikipedia
Sasha Cohen.Born: October 26, 1984 (age 29), Westwood, Los Angeles, California, United States

Scott Moir.label: Scott Moir
Scott Moir.description: Scott Moir is a Canadian ice dancer who competes with Tessa Virtue. Moir and Virtue are the 2010 Olympic champions, the 2010 and 2012 World Champions, the 2008 & 2012 Four Continents Champions, the 2006 ... Wikipedia

Sergey Nikolayevich Volkov.label: Sergey Nikolayevich Volkov
Sergey Nikolayevich Volkov.description: Sergey Nikolayevich Volkov was a Soviet figure skater. He was the 1975 World champion and an Honored Sports Master. Wikipedia

Shizuka Arakawa.label: Shizuka Arakawa
Shizuka Arakawa.description:
Shizuka Arakawa is a Japanese figure skater.
She is the 2006 Olympic Champion in Ladies Singles and the 2004 World Champion. Wikipedia

Sjoukje Dijkstra.label: Sjoukje Dijkstra
Sjoukje Dijkstra.description: Sjoukje Rosalinde Dijkstra is a Dutch figure skater. She is the 1964 Olympic champion in ladies' singles, the 1960 Olympic silver medalist, a three-time World champion, five-time European champion, and the six-time Dutch national champion. Wikipedia

Sonja Henie.label: Sonja Henie
Sonja Henie.description: Sonja Henie was a Norwegian figure skater and film star. She was a three-time Olympic Champion in Ladies Singles, a ten-time World Champion and a six-time European Champion. Wikipedia

Tatiana Navka.label: Tatiana Navka
Tatiana Navka.description: Tatyana Aleksandrovna Navka is a Russian ice dancer. With partner Roman Kostomarov, she is the 2006 Olympic champion, a two-time World champion, a three-time Grand Prix Final champion, and a three-time European champion. Wikipedia

Tonya Harding.label: Tonya Harding
Tonya Harding.description: Tonya Maxene Harding is an American figure skating champion, a two-time Olympian, and a two-time Skate America Champion. In 1991, she won the U.S. Figure Skating Championships and placed second in the World Championships. Wikipedia
Movies and TV shows: Figure Skating Superstars Brian Boitano and FriendsMore

Ulrich Salchow.label: Ulrich Salchow
Ulrich Salchow.description:
Karl Emil Julius Ulrich Salchow was a Swedish figure skater, who dominated the sport in the first decade of the 20th century.
Salchow won the World Figure Skating Championships ten times, from 1901 to 1905, and from 1907 to 1911. Wikipedia

Trixi Schuba.label: Trixi Schuba
Trixi Schuba.description: Beatrix "Trixi" Schuba is an Austrian former competitive figure skater who competed in ladies' singles. She is a six-time Austrian national champion, a two-time European champion, a two-time World champion, and 1972 Olympic champion. Wikipedia

Uwe Bewersdorf.label: Uwe Bewersdorf
Uwe Bewersdorf.description:
Uwe Bewerdorf is a German former pair skater.
Uwe Bewersdorf was a team with Manuela Mager. He started to skate with the age of 7 at the club Betriebs-Sportbund-Gemeinschaft Post Dresden. Later the club was renamed into SC Einheit Dresden. Wikipedia

Uwe Kagelmann.label: Uwe Kagelmann
Uwe Kagelmann.description:
Uwe Kagelmann is a German pair skater. Competing with Manuela Groß, he was twice bronze medalist at the Olympics. He later became a figure skating coach.
The pair skated for the SV Dynamo club and represented East Germany. Wikipedia

Brian Boitano.label: Brian Boitano
Brian Boitano.description: Brian Anthony Boitano is an American figure skater from Sunnyvale, California. He is the 1988 Olympic champion, the 1986 and 1988 World Champion, and the 1985–1988 U.S. National Champion. He turned professional following the 1988 season. Wikipedia
Brian Boitano.Born: October 22, 1963 (age 50), Mountain View, California, United States
Awards: Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Performance in Classical Music or Dance Programming
Nominations: Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Choreography

Midori Ito.label: Midori Ito
Midori Ito.description: Midori Ito or Midori Itō is a Japanese former figure skater. She is the 1989 World champion and the 1992 Olympic silver medalist. She is the first woman to land a triple/triple jump combination and a triple axel in competition. Wikipedia
Movies: Olympic Figure Skating Greatest Performances in History Vol. 1

Carol Heiss.label: Carol Heiss
Carol Heiss.description: Carol Elizabeth Heiss Jenkins is an American figure skater and former actress. She is the 1960 Olympic Champion in Ladies Singles, 1956 Olympic silver medalist and five-time World Champion. Wikipedia
Carol Heiss.Born: January 20, 1940 (age 74), New York City, New York, United States
Movies: Snow White and the Three Stooges
Olympic Figure Skating Greatest Performances in History Vol. 2

Aaron Parchem.label: Aaron Parchem
Aaron Parchem.description: Aaron Parchem is an American former pair skater. He competed in the 2006 Winter Olympics with partner Marcy Hinzmann. Wikipedia

Adam Rippon.label: Adam Rippon
Adam Rippon.description: Adam Rippon is an American figure skater. He is the 2010 Four Continents champion, the 2012 U.S. silver medalist, the 2008 and 2009 World Junior champion, the 2008 U.S. junior national champion, and the 2007–2008 Junior Grand Prix Final champion. Wikipedia

Agnes Zawadzki.label: Agnes Zawadzki
Agnes Zawadzki.description: Agnes Zawadzki is an American figure skater. She is the 2012 Rostelecom Cup bronze medalist and a two-time U.S. national bronze medalist. As a junior, she was a two-time World Junior medalist and the 2010 U.S. Junior champion. Wikipedia

Albertina Noyes.label: Albertina Noyes
Albertina Noyes.description: Albertina Natalie "Tina" Noyes is an American former figure skater. She won the silver medal at the U.S. Figure Skating Championships four times and is the 1967 North American bronze medalist. Wikipedia

Alex Shibutani.label: Alex Shibutani
Alex Shibutani.description: Alex Hideo Shibutani is an American ice dancer. With his sister Maia Shibutani, he is the 2011 World bronze medalist, 2011 Four Continents silver medalist, 2011 NHK Trophy champion, 2009 World Junior ... Wikipedia

Alexander Johnson (figure skater).label: Alexander Johnson
Alexander Johnson (figure skater).description:
Alexander Johnson is an American figure skater. He is the 2013 Challenge Cup silver medalist and won gold at the 2008 ISU Junior Grand Prix in the Czech Republic.
In the 2011–2012 season, Johnson also competed in pair skating with Danielle Viola. Wikipedia

Alexe Gilles.label: Alexe Gilles
Alexe Gilles.description: Alexe Gilles is an American-born Canadian figure skater. She is the 2008 Junior Grand Prix Final bronze medalist and the 2008 U.S. national junior champion. Wikipedia

Alice Cook (figure skater).label: Alice Cook
Alice Cook (figure skater).description: Alice Maxine Cook is an American sports reporter and former pair skater. With partner William Fauver, she is the 1976 U.S. silver medalist. They represented the United States at the 1976 Winter Olympics, where they placed 12th. Wikipedia

Alissa Czisny.label: Alissa Czisny
Alissa Czisny.description: Alissa Czisny is an American figure skater. She is the 2010 Grand Prix Final champion, a two-time Skate Canada champion, the 2011 Skate America champion, and a two-time U.S. national champion. Wikipedia
Alissa Czisny.Born: June 25, 1987 (age 26), Bowling Green, Ohio, United States

Allison Reed.label: Allison Reed
Allison Reed.description: Allison Lynn Reed is an American ice dancer. She currently competes with Vasili Rogov for Israel. From 2009 to 2011, she competed with Otar Japaridze for Georgia. Wikipedia

Amanda Evora.label: Amanda Evora
Amanda Evora.description: Amanda Evora is an American pair skater. She competed with Mark Ladwig. They are two-time U.S. silver medalists, 2012 U.S. bronze medalists and two-time U.S. pewter medalists. Wikipedia
Amanda Evora.Born: November 17, 1984 (age 29), New York City, New York, United States

Amanda Dobbs.label: Amanda Dobbs
Amanda Dobbs.description: Amanda J. Dobbs is an American figure skater. As a single skater, she placed fourth at the 2010 Four Continents Championships. She also competed in pair skating on the national senior level with Joseph Jacobsen . Wikipedia

Amber Corwin.label: Amber Corwin
Amber Corwin.description: Amber Corwin is an American figure skater. She is the 1999 Four Continents silver medalist and 2004 bronze medalist. Wikipedia

Amber Kole.label: Amber Kole
Amber Kole.description: Amber Kole is a retired American pair skater. She competed with partner Nicholas Kole at the Senior level. They placed 16th at the 2007 U.S. Figure Skating Championships and 13th at the 2008 U.S. Figure Skating Championships. Wikipedia

Andrea Gardiner.label: Andrea Gardiner
Andrea Gardiner.description: Andrea Gardiner is an American former competitive figure skater. She is the 2000 Nebelhorn Trophy bronze medalist and competed twice at the Four Continents Championships, placing 8th in 2000 and 11th in 2002. She was coached by Kitty Carruthers. Wikipedia

Andrew Stroukoff.label: Andrew Stroukoff
Andrew Stroukoff.description: Andrew George "Andy" Stroukoff is an American former competitive ice dancer. With partner Susan Kelley, he represented the United States at the 1976 Winter Olympics, where they placed 17th. Wikipedia
Andrew Stroukoff.Born: April 27, 1950 (age 63), Trenton, New Jersey, United States

Andree Anderson.label: Andree Anderson
Andree Anderson.description: Andree Anderson is an American ice dancer. Wikipedia

Angela Lien.label: Angela Lien
Angela Lien.description: Angela "Angie" Lien is an American figure skater. She is the 2003 Winter Universiade silver medalist. Wikipedia

Angela Maxwell.label: Angela Maxwell
Angela Maxwell.description: Angela Yuka Maxwell is an American figure skater. She is the 2008 U.S. Junior Silver Medalist and the 2007 U.S. Novice Champion. Wikipedia

Angela Nikodinov.label: Angela Nikodinov
Angela Nikodinov.description: Angela Nikodinov, is an American figure skater. She is the 2000 Four Continents champion. Wikipedia
Angela Nikodinov.Born: May 9, 1980 (age 33), Spartanburg, South Carolina, United States

Ann Patrice McDonough.label: Ann Patrice McDonough
Ann Patrice McDonough.description: Ann Patrice McDonough is an American retired competitive figure skater. She is the 2002 World Junior Champion and the 2003 U.S. pewter medalist. McDonough retired from skating in 2004. Wikipedia

Armin Mahbanoozadeh.label: Armin Mahbanoozadeh
Armin Mahbanoozadeh.description: Armin Mahbanoozadeh is an American figure skater. He is the 2010 Skate America bronze medalist and the 2012 U.S. national pewter medalist. He is also a two-time Junior Grand Prix Final medalist and the 2007 U.S. novice champion. Wikipedia

Ashley Wagner.label: Ashley Wagner
Ashley Wagner.description: {{Infobox figure skater | name = Ashley Wagner | image = Cup of Russia 2010 - Ashley Wagner.jpg | caption = Wagner at the 2010 Cup of Russia practice | country = United States | fullname = | birth_date ... Wikipedia

Arthur Vaughn Jr..label: Arthur Vaughn Jr.
Arthur Vaughn Jr..description:
Arthur Vaughn Jr. was an American figure skater. He won the United States Figure Skating Championships in 1943. He was inducted into the U.S. Figure Skating Hall Of Fame in 2001.
He was the brother of Jane Vaughn. Wikipedia

Beata Handra.label: Beata Handra
Beata Handra.description: Beata Handra is an American former competitive ice dancer. With partner and husband Charles Sinek, she is the 1999–2002 U.S. national pewter medalist and placed as high as fourth at the Four Continents Championships. Wikipedia

Austin Kanallakan.label: Austin Kanallakan
Austin Kanallakan.description: Austin Kanallakan is an American former competitive figure skater. He won three gold medals on the ISU Junior Grand Prix series and silver at the 2006 JGP Final. Wikipedia
Austin Kanallakan.Born: May 23, 1991 (age 22), Woodland Hills, Los Angeles, California, United States

Beatrisa Liang.label: Beatrisa Liang
Beatrisa Liang.description: Beatrisa "Bebe" Liang is an American figure skater. She is the 2006 Four Continents bronze medalist, 2006 Nebelhorn Trophy champion, and 2007 U.S. national pewter medalist. Wikipedia
Beatrisa Liang.Born: March 31, 1988 (age 25), Tarzana, Los Angeles, California, United States

Beatrix Loughran.label: Beatrix Loughran
Beatrix Loughran.description: Beatrix S. Loughran was an American figure skater who competed in single skating and pair skating. She is the only American to win three Olympic medals in figure skating. She is a six-time National champion. Her pairs partner was Sherwin Badger. Wikipedia

Becky Bereswill.label: Becky Bereswill
Becky Bereswill.description: Rebecca Ann "Becky" Bereswill is an American figure skater. She is the 2008 Junior Grand Prix Final champion. Wikipedia

Benjamin Agosto.label: Benjamin Agosto
Benjamin Agosto.description: Benjamin Alexandro Agosto is an American ice dancer. With partner Tanith Belbin, Agosto is the 2006 Olympic silver medalist, a four-time World medalist, the 2004–2006 Four Continents champion, and 2004–2008 U.S. champion. Wikipedia
